The 2023 off-leash season started at Ann Morrison Park and Optimist Youth Sports Complex on Wednesday, Nov. 1, which ends Feb. 28, 2024, and now at Simplot Sports Complex on Tuesday, Nov. 21, which ends Feb. 15, 2024. item.title: The Best Water-Based Pomades - Us Weekly
item.description: Buying Guide: Water-Based Pomades Water-Based Pomade vs. Oil-Based Pomade Oil-based pomades First, let’s talk about oil-based pomades. As their name suggests, these products are made with oily ingredients, like mineral oil or petroleum jelly at their core. This oily base allows these products to have a stronger, more resilient hold compared to water-based pomades. They provide a greasy, slick look, making them perfect for vintage hairstyles. The biggest disadvantage to oil-based pomades is that they’re a pain to wash out.
